<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870427-0045 </DOCNO><HL> Italian Trade Deficit Narrows</HL><DD> 04/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROPMONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON) </IN><DATELINE> ROME  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Italy's trade deficit narrowed to the equivalent of $352.9 million in March from $859.6 million a year earlier, converting the lira at its current rate, the State Statistical Institute said.    Exports increased 11%, to $1.08 billion, while imports rose 5.1%, to $1.12 billion.    In 1987's first quarter, the institute said, the trade gap narrowed to $3.13 billion from $4.45 billion a year earlier. </TEXT></DOC>